Date: Sun 14 Oct 2012
Source: The Daily Star [edited]
http://www.thedailystar.net/newDesign/news-details.php?nid=253664


Farmers worried as disease wreaks havoc on rice
-----------------------------------------------
Massive pest (stem borer) attack and stem rot disease are wreaking havoc on the transplanted aman [wet season lowland rice] in Taraganj, Rangpur division. Frustration has gripped the farmers. At least 20 to 25 percent of the plants have been badly affected.

The farmers said that plants at different villages are drying up. "If the situation continues, we will suffer huge losses." They failed to prevent spread of stem disease and pest attack despite spraying insecticides. According to the district agriculture officials, aman has been cultivated on 9800 hectares [24 216 acres] in Taraganj.

[see photo at http://www.thedailystar.net/newDesign/photo_gallery.php?pid=253664]

